{{Other persons|Mark Williams}} {{Infobox person | name = Mark Williams | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1959|8|22|52 years}} | birth_place = [[Bromsgrove]], Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom | death_date = | birth_name = | othername = | occupation = Actor, comedian, presenter, screenwriter | yearsactive = 1982âpresent | website = }} '''Mark Williams''' (born 22 August 1959) is an English actor, comedian, screenwriter and presenter. He is best known as one of the stars of the popular BBC [[sketch show]] ''[[The Fast Show]]'', as well as for his role as [[Arthur Weasley]] in the [[Harry Potter (films)|''Harry Potter'' films]].
==Life and career== Williams was born in [[Bromsgrove]]. In 2007, Williams appeared in the film adaptation of [[Neil Gaiman]]'s ''[[Stardust (2007 film)|Stardust]]'' alongside [[Michelle Pfeiffer]], [[Robert De Niro]] and [[Claire Danes]].
Williams has also presented several documentary programmes: ''Mark Williams' Big Bangs'' on the history of explosives, a follow-up to previous series ''Mark Williams on the Rails'', ''Industrial Revelations'' and ''More Industrial Revelations''.
He is a supporter of both [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] and [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]<ref>[http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/mark-williams-captain-of-industry-507748.html Mark Williams: Captain of industry from independent.co.uk]</ref> football clubs.
